body:
@jerryshao Agree on adding a whitelist, so I'll work on this.

Regarding the ordering. For our use case, it would make sense to have a default configuration value, set in config file, which can be overridden by corresponding environment variable if it was added into whitelist. In this case, it's still under control of system administrator, who does a setup of Livy and decides what should be user-specific configuration, and it's configurable by user, who runs a job. So, it means that environment variable will have a priority over configuration option. 
Are any issues related with this?
